### 2026-06-01T07:30:00Z DEC session-start-hook-convention

The repo's AGENTS.md is the session-start convention. ACCEPTANCE_CRITERIA.md re-acknowledgment is enforced by an `ACK` line append to this DECISIONS.log at every session start, including the sha256 of ACCEPTANCE_CRITERIA.md + PLAN.md. If hashes change without a `CHANGE` entry, session is in violation and must halt.

### 2026-06-01T07:30:00Z DEC test-id-taxonomy

Task ids `P-<phase>-<seq>`. Acceptance ids `AC-<class>-<seq>`. Human test ids `HTC-<section>-<seq>`. Autonomous test ids `ATC-<class>-<seq>`. Defect fix ids `P-FIX-<seq>`. Operator-action ids `P-OP-<seq>`. These ids are stable for the entire closeout run.

### 2026-06-01T07:30:00Z DEC operator-gates-fallback-policy

For each P-OP-* (CZ-006 portal domain, CZ-008 Vapi config, OP-001 Nexxus cutover, OP-002 per-customer creds, OP-003 sidecars), agent will (a) surface the gate explicitly in the closeout report, (b) document the fallback chosen (e.g. plugin-native renderer if Metabase deferred; federation_query removed from launch tool surface if MindsDB deferred), (c) ensure the fallback is itself green with evidence, (d) NOT make a launch claim if any launch-visible surface depends on an open operator gate.

### 2026-06-01T07:30:00Z DEC use-of-subagents

Operator's prompt explicitly authorized subagent use. Closeout will use:
- `code-reviewer` subagent for adversarial verification at end of each P-CZ / P-SRS PR before merge, and for the final closeout review (AC-FC-005).
- `Explore` subagents for surface sweeps where multiple parallel reads accelerate without polluting main context.
- `Workflow` tool for fan-out tasks like per-profile readiness probe, per-screen sweep, or per-tenant isolation verification if such parallelism is needed.

